race.comment: HOT SEA (4) sets a decent standard resuming off a 1.8L defeat in the Group 3 Chairman's Stakes on debut. Won a recent Cranbourne jumpout and will be naturally improved. Maps for the run of the race and Mott stays aboard. Has seemingly scared off most of the apparent main opposition and looks set to enjoy a soft kill for his maiden success first up. For those looking for an upset, NOMOREKAYE (11) debuts off a trial win at this course on October 3. BLAZE AWAY (1) placed on debut at Seymour. While he was safely held last start, all other public appearances before that suggested he does have ability. EMANATING (8) next elect. Placed on debut at Sale back in July. Could be improvement getting back on top of the ground.
